Legal_Issue: Credibility assessment and reasonableness of state protection finding
Credibility_Assessment: Doubted due to lack of corroborating evidence
Evidence_Type: Absence of removal notices, medical reports
Basis_of_Claim: Persecution due to Roma ethnicity in Hungary
Key_Factor_in_Determination: Lack of credible evidence and insufficient effectiveness of state protection
Legal_Standard: Credibility findings reviewed on reasonableness; state protection must be adequate, not perfect
Decision_Review_Issue: Whether RPD erred in credibility finding and state protection assessment
Governing_Rule_or_Provision: IRPA subsection 72(1); principles of refugee protection under international law
Cause_of_Refusal: Lack of credibility and inadequate demonstration of ineffective state protection
Evidentiary_Issues: Failure to provide removal notices and medical records
Legal_Defense_or_Challenge: Allegation of unreasonable credibility and state protection findings
